    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-30T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="423"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0061/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-30T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 30, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 31—2:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>978. Foreign Office has just orally advised the Embassy that the Diplomatic Corps
                    at Kuibyshev will return to Moscow within a month.</p>
                <pb facs="0569" n="557" xml:id="pg_557"/>
                <p>When asked whether this decision was to be regarded as confidential until
                    announced Embassy informed that Foreign Office was today advising the Diplomatic
                    Corps.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
